			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">With GoD AA's...our Best Weapon DPS Combo?<a name="31280"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 29 04 6:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The guild I'm in on Maelin recently entered Potime and today(yesterday really) we started on Phase 4 Gods.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I'm currently the top bard in DKP, and we only have 2 other bards besides myself, so I've got a fairly decent pick between weapons that drop.  I do not plan to spend any DKP until I get new weapons first.
<br />

<br />
There are 3 major considerations, as there always were.
<br />

<br />
Ethereal Destroyer, Songblade of the Eternal, and Edge of Eternity.
<br />

<br />
Now previously, SoE and EoE were considered the &quot;Prime Duo&quot;, that is, the best 2 weapons for a bard to duel wield.
<br />

<br />
However...GoD introduced a new AA, Weapon Affinity, that significantly increases the rate at which weapons Proc.  WA 5 could turn ED into one h*ll of a weapon.
<br />

<br />
As bards, our biggest weakness in our melee DPS is our very weak ability to double attack.  However, since Weapon Procs go off Based on set time intervals randomly, the number of hits we do is irrelevant to the amount we proc.  Thus, a proc'ing weapon is far more valueble to a bard than other classes.
<br />

<br />
I can't see much use for Edge of Eternity's Percussion mod except Lazyness --- I don't have to swap a drum when pulling a mob with HoS.  Cept I still prolly would cause drum still better.  With AE resists --- same deal.  You want the best so you use drum.
<br />

<br />
So anyway, I was thinking ED in Main-hand and SoTE in Off-hand.  Any thoughts?  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
