				<td colspan="2"><span>dude your totally missing the point of the EoE the 2.5 mod on the EoE isent ment to be used for AE resists, with P4 / P5 mobs doing AE's with -250 / - 300 on checks you have to use a rathe drum period. the intended purpose of the EoE is for the bard that is going pure melle / tanking and in no way focusing on group songs, its is a pure dps weapon when coupled with 4 chants + the 1 min brass DoT a bard can easly do 240+ dps and by the time you have a EoE you will be a 5-6k unbuffed bard and can now sub as a tank, its a phenominal weapon and i would choose it over a ED any time, I would also mention the ED has a lowerd process rate, you can check it out on the steel warrior, I would go with a EoE over a ED any time, also rember that becouse you are relying heavly on the process of the ED, for it to be effictive it must be used in the main hand, and then when a songblade drops you will be losing dps by having it in the offhand beacous your trying to salvage the dps off the ED (BTW this topic was allready discussed on the steel warrior as to a ED or EoE. while it was shown that the ED with multuiple combat effects and WA5 can be a effective DPS weapon, the general consession was that the EoE was the more superior weapon, and keep in mind the DPS of a bard chant was never figured into the equation)</span></td>
