				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"> I can understand the interest in seeing our best DPS combo, although i dont understand the relevance; </span></blockquote> 
<br />

<br />
2 Days ago, on our 2nd attempt ever, my guild Wiped to Sayryn in time, getting her down to 1% health.  Yeah, 1%.
<br />

<br />
No, DPS may not be our primary Focus.  But it is <i> A </i> Focus.  Had the Bard who was with the rest of the melee's proc'd, say, 10-20 750 DD procs(Not unreasonable for a 10 minute fight), that extra 15,000 damage would have meant Sayryn would be laying on the ground, dead, as opposed to regening back up to 100% and staring at our corpses. (It was my job to be protecting clerics and covering AE resists so not melee'ing).
<br />

<br />
So, does Sayryn wipe everyone at 1% alot?  No, probably not.
<br />

<br />
But I can't count the number of times in the past I've won an LDoN hard in the last 5 minutes left.  I always melee for Hards to make every bit of Difference.  The better my DPS is, even if it's not the primary contribution to the group, the faster mobs die, and thus, the less time we take to do the adventure.  HP/AC won't make that sort of difference for me --- I VERY rarely die in ldon's, even hards.  Sure, it'd save a little cleric mana when I take a few hits pulling, but unless the tank or cleric sucks and is OOM constantly, that makes no difference at all.  My DPS, however, makes a difference.
<br />

<br />

<br />
And PS btw We did kill Sayryn next attempt :P.</span></td>
