Well look at it this way. With offensive AAs and CE +10(which includes WA5), at 2.8m, you'll proc say, 1680 damage more every minute than the EoE. Which, DPS-wise, amounts to 28 DPS more, in procs. Since you're comparing a 1.0 Ratio to a .75 Ratio, the question is, will 33% more damage on one of -our- weapons result in a 28 or greater DPS increase? </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Tounces where are you getting you'r math? And also remember you get 1/2 the procs if you offhand a weapon. Look at the weapons the easiest way(before AA and mods), EoE procs 2x a min. (also the EoE stuns up to lvl 68 , owns many caster mobs). Thats 300 a min from a proc. The ED does 1.8, thats 1350. The diff between the 2 is 1050. Then you have the sh*t ratio of the ED and all of a suddon its not sounding too good for the ED right? 
<br />

<br />
The only way a ED MIGHT out DPS a EoE is if you mainhand it. Offhand and the ED is pathetic. Plus relying on a MR proc to do your DPS can be very chancy vs straight ratio.
<br />

<br />
The advantage of also being able to keep melee up WHILE twisting DoTs and or HOS is also very nice. Thats all play style though.
<br />

<br />
In the end I choose the EoE simply because of the ability to do HOS/DOT while fighting. DPS was so close if was a complete non-factor.
<br />

<br />
Also as far as worrying about using a drum vs the EoE for AE resists. Soon your guildmates will be getting 500 resists with just basic resist buffs. Much less with Bard song. You certainly will not need the drum mod for AE resists if you are up front in a melee group. If your clerics and such are in dire need of resists they will prolly be getting PoV anyway.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
